# Water Directory Project - Cursor Rules

## Stack
- Next.js 14 App Router
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- Supabase (PostgreSQL + PostGIS)
- Vercel deployment
- GitHub version control

## Project Purpose
UK water quality directory. User enters postcode → app returns 
tap water chemical data (nitrates, lead, fluoride, chlorine) 
and sewage spill info for their area.

## Architecture: "God Mode" Postcode Lookup
1. User enters postcode
2. Strip spaces, ping postcodes.io API → returns LSOA code
3. Query Supabase water_zones table matching zone_id = LSOA
4. Query Supabase chemical_readings table matching zone_id
5. Return data to WaterScorecard component
6. Fallback to regional averages if no local data

## Supabase Tables
- suppliers: 25 UK water companies
- postcodes: 2.7M UK postcodes with coordinates (PostGIS)
- water_zones: LSOA boundary codes mapped to suppliers
- chemical_readings: chemical data keyed on zone_id (UPPERCASE)
- sewage_spills: spill records with location coords

## Critical Supabase Rules
- NEVER put Supabase service_role key in client-side code
- anon key only in frontend, service_role in API routes only
- All Supabase fetch logic lives in app/api/ routes, never components
- RLS policies must allow public SELECT or frontend shows 0 results
- Always upload water_zones BEFORE chemical_readings (foreign key)
- Batch uploads in groups of 200-500 rows

## File Structure
- app/api/water/route.ts → postcode lookup (server-side)
- app/api/leads/route.ts → lead form submissions
- components/WaterScorecard.tsx → results display
- components/WaterLookup.tsx → search form
- app/page.tsx → main page

## Environment Variables
- NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL
- NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
- SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY (server/API routes only)

## UK Legal Limits for Chemical RAG Status
- Nitrates: 50 mg/l
- Lead: 10 µg/l
- Fluoride: 1.5 mg/l
- Chlorine: 1.0 mg/l
Green = <50% of limit, Amber = 50-80%, Red = >80%

## Data Sources
- streamwaterdata.co.uk → primary CSV source for all water companies
- postcodes.io → free postcode to LSOA translation API
- ONS Postcode Directory → 2.7M postcode coordinates
- Ofwat NAV shapefiles → water supplier boundary zones

## Live Data (already in Supabase)
- Thames Water (PDF extraction → custom Zone IDs)
- Southern Water (Stream CSV → LSOA)
- Cambridge Water (Stream CSV → LSOA)

